ce, and use `assign` for combinational logic, avoiding `always @(*)` blocks unless strictly necessary (which it is not here).\n6. **Advice on Syntax Errors**: A common error is incorrect indexing when interpreting the K-map, especially relating $a, b, c, d$ to the binary index. Another risk is forgetting that `a` is the MSB of the row grouping ($ab$) and $c$ is the MSB of the column grouping ($cd$). The derived minterm expression covers all 16 possibilities correctly, ensuring all required conditions are met.\n\n*Self-Correction during K-map interpretation*: The testbench provided in the prompt attempted complex logical reductions, which are error-prone. The most robust method is to translate the truth table derived from the K-map directly into an ORed sum of the required minterms, as done in the final code structure, ensuring all 1s are captured and all 0s are implicitly handled by omitting them from the OR sum.",
